      section.content
        h2 What will you learn?
        | My goal is to teach you all you need to get a job in tech. We will start with creating websites, after that we will be building 
        a(href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Single-page_application" target="_blank") Single-page applications
        | , and finish the course with server and database programming in 
        a(href="http://nodejs.org/" target="_blank") Node.js
        |  and 
        a(href="http://www.mongodb.org/" target="_blank") MongoDB
        | . In the final unit you will work on your individual portfolio and we will exercise job applications and interview questions.
        br
        br
        | Once a week you will get a task and instructions delivered simply into your inbox. 
        | Every week we will learn a new concept and apply it right away to a concrete real life project. 
        | Should you ever get stuck, I'm always just a short email away to help you succeed.
        | Each month we are going to start a new project. So that by the end of the course you will have a portfolio of 12 projects and a 
        a(href="https://github.com/" target="_blank") Github
        |  account full of open source code ready to apply for your first job in tech.
        br
        br
